estment%20plan.%20It%20could%20add%20to%20Indiana's%20growing%20fleet%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famazon-google-microsoft-ai-future-data-centers-monopoly-tech-industry-2024-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edata%20centers%3C%2Fa%3E%20under%20construction%20by%20companies%20including%20Amazon%2C%20Microsoft%2C%20and%20Google%2C%20which%20need%20huge%20amounts%20of%20computing%20power%20for%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-ai-is-changing-everything%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eartificial%20intelligence%3C%2Fa%3E%20boom.%20The%20growth%20risks%20saddling%20residents%20with%20hundreds%20of%20millions%20of%20dollars%20in%20additional%20costs%20through%20higher%20energy%20bills.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20situation%20has%20set%20off%20a%20debate%20in%20Indiana%20over%20who%20should%20foot%20the%20bill%20for%20the%20new%20power%20plants%20and%20transmission%20infrastructure%20needed%20to%20serve%20data%20centers.%20A%20bill%20moving%20through%20the%20Indiana%20legislature%20would%20require%20tech%20firms%20like%20Amazon%2C%20Microsoft%2C%20and%20Google%20to%20cover%2080%25%20of%20project%20costs%2C%20which%2C%20if%20enacted%2C%20would%20make%20it%20the%20first%20state%20to%20do%20so.%20At%20the%20same%20time%2C%20the%20bill%20would%20allow%20Indiana%20utilities%20to%20try%20and%20pass%20the%20costs%20of%20building%20smaller%20nuclear%20reactors%20to%20customers.%20Tech%20companies%20hope%20these%20early-stage%20energy%20solutions%20could%20someday%20supply%20cleaner%2C%20around-the-clock%20power%20to%20data%20centers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20a%20mixed%20bag%20for%20Indiana%20residents%20that%20consumer%20advocacy%20groups%20oppose%2C%20and%20underscores%20a%20dilemma%20many%20states%20across%20the%20country%20are%20confronting%3A%20how%20to%20hold%20tech%20firms%20accountable%20for%20their%20power-hungry%20data%20centers%20and%20their%20promises%20that%20AI%20will%20be%20powered%20by%20green%20energy.%20So%20far%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Futilities-ai-natural-gas-power-microsoft-meta-amazon-2025-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efossil%20fuels%3C%2Fa%3E%20like%20natural%20gas%20and%20coal%20plants%20are%20expected%20to%20meet%20the%20demand.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20companies%20want%20to%20build%20a%20data%20center%20here%2C%20and%20we%20have%20to%20build%20new%20power%20generation%20for%20them%2C%20then%20they%20need%20to%20share%20in%20that%20risk%2C%26quot%3B%20Indiana%20Rep.%20Ed%20Soliday%2C%20a%20Republican%20who%20authored%20the%20bill%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider.%20%26quot%3BThere%20are%20a%20couple%20of%20data%20center%20folks%20that%20have%20said%2C%20'Oh%20no%2C%20that's%20not%20fair.'%20Yes%2C%20it%20is.%20Grandma%20down%20the%20street%20shouldn't%20have%20to%20pay%20for%20your%20dreams.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22616fe254-6a2e-4668-8042-b5c296ddf703%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EIndiana%20courts%20power-hungry%20data%20centers%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20Indiana%20doesn't%20top%20the%20list%20of%20major%20US%20data%20center%20hubs%2C%20the%20Rust%20Belt%20state%20is%20emerging%20as%20another%20player%20for%20many%20reasons.%20Indiana%20has%20a%20reliable%20power%20supply%20from%20coal%20and%20natural%20gas%20and%20can%20draw%20electricity%20from%20two%20regional%20grids.%20That%20state%20has%20a%20low%20risk%20of%20natural%20disasters%20that%20could%20disrupt%20that%20supply.%20Indiana%20lawmakers%20in%202019%20exempted%20data%20center%20equipment%20and%20energy%20use%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fiedc.in.gov%2Findiana-advantages%2Finvestments%2Fdata-center-sales-tax-exemption%2Foverview%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efrom%20sales%20taxes%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Land%20is%20also%20cheaper%20than%20other%20parts%20of%20the%20country.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThose%20perks%20have%20attracted%20large%20data%20centers%20to%20northern%20Indiana.%20Last%20year%2C%20Amazon%20Web%20Services%20started%20construction%20on%20an%20%2411%20billion%20data%20center%20campus%20in%20New%20Carlisle.%20Google%20announced%20plans%20to%20build%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cityoffortwayne.org%2Flatest-news%2F5715-google-announces-2-billion-data-center-in-fort-wayne.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%242%20billion%20data%20center%20in%20Fort%20Wayne%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Microsoft%20is%20planning%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fiedc.in.gov%2Fevents%2Fnews%2Fdetails%2F2024%2F06%2F04%2Fgov-holcomb-announces-plans-for-new-1b-microsoft-data-center-in-northwest-indiana%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%241%20billion%20data%20center%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20LaPorte%3B%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.datacenterdynamics.com%2Fen%2Fnews%2Fmeta-to-develop-data-center-campus-in-jeffersonville-indiana%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMeta%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20investing%20%24800%20million%20in%20a%20campus%20in%20southern%20Indiana%20that%20could%20operate%20by%202026.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EProjects%20in%20the%20pipeline%20could%20consume%20more%20electricity%20than%20the%20nearly%207%20million%20residents%20in%20Indiana%20combined%20by%202035%2C%20according%20to%20forecasts%20by%20state%20utilities%20analyzed%20by%20the%20Citizens%20Action%20Coalition%20of%20Indiana%2C%20an%20advocacy%20group%20that%20opposes%20data%20center%20development%20in%20the%20state.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20coalition%20has%20called%20for%20a%20moratorium%20on%20new%20data%20centers%20until%20state%20leaders%20can%20study%20their%20potential%20impact%20on%20the%20electric%20grid%20and%20utility%20bills.%20But%20as%20more%20projects%20enter%20the%20pipeline%20with%20support%20from%20state%20officials%2C%20the%20coalition%20last%20year%20intervened%20in%20negotiations%20between%20a%20utility%20and%20the%20data%20center%20industry%20%E2%80%94%20including%20Amazon%20Web%20Services%2C%20Google%2C%20and%20Microsoft%20%E2%80%94%20aimed%20at%20ensuring%20the%20companies%20pay%20a%20fair%20share%20for%20their%20energy%20use%20and%20associated%20power%20grid%20infrastructure%20upgrades.%20The%20parties%20in%20November%20reached%20an%20agreement%20aimed%20at%20shielding%20Indiana%20customers%20from%20some%20of%20the%20extra%20costs%20by%20requiring%20large%20data%20centers%20each%20month%20to%20pay%20at%20least%2080%25%20of%20their%20contracted%20electricity%20use%2C%20even%20if%20they%20don't%20use%20it.%20New%20transmission%20infrastructure%20and%20power%20generation%20to%20serve%20data%20centers%20could%20cost%20up%20to%20%241%20billion%2C%20the%20agreement%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIndiana%20regulators%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.indianamichiganpower.com%2Fcompany%2Fnews%2Fview%3FreleaseID%3D10036%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eapproved%20the%20settlement%20in%20February%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20utility%2C%20Indiana%20Michigan%20Power%2C%20initiated%20the%20changes%20to%20what%20its%20big%20industrial%20energy%20users%20pay%20after%20forecasting%20that%20data%20centers%20could%20increase%20peak%20electricity%20demand%20by%20150%25%20by%202030%2C%20to%20more%20than%207%2C000%20megawatts.%20That's%20equivalent%20to%20power%20for%20about%204.6%20million%20residents%20in%20the%20state%20or%20two-thirds%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.census.gov%2Fquickfacts%2Ffact%2Ftable%2FIN%2FPST045224%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EIndiana's%20entire%20population%3C%2Fa%3E.%20And%20that's%20just%20one%20utility's%20service%20area.%20The%20Northern%20Indiana%20Public%20Service%20Company's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.in.gov%2Fiurc%2Ffiles%2FNIPSCO-2024-Integrated-Resource-Plan-Document.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elatest%20forecast%3C%2Fa%3E%20shows%20data%20centers%20could%20double%20its%20energy%20demand%20by%202035.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAndrew%20Williamson%2C%20Indiana%20Michigan%20Power's%20directory%20of%20regulatory%20services%2C%20said%20in%20written%20testimony%20that%20the%20magnitude%20of%20demand%20for%20electricity%20was%20unprecedented%20and%20unlike%20any%20previous%20energy%20load%20additions%20the%20utility%20had%20ever%20experienced.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22944fed1d-b28e-498e-a1fc-cf1aa4567a97%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3E'More%20harm%20than%20good'%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ERather%20than%20striking%20deals%20utility%20by%20utility%2C%20consumer%20advocates%20said%20a%20statewide%20law%20could%20better%20protect%20Indiana%20residents%20from%20rising%20energy%20bills%20associated%20with%20new%20data%20centers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20bill%20moving%20through%20the%20state%20legislature%20falls%20short%2C%20said%20Ben%20Inskeep%2C%20program%20director%20of%20the%20Citizens%20Action%20Coalition%20of%20Indiana.%20He%20said%20the%20bill%20contains%20a%20loophole%2C%20in%20that%20it%20doesn't%20cover%20special%20contracts%20utilities%20can%20negotiate%20with%20data%20centers%20for%20electricity%20rates.%20The%20bill%20also%20would%20create%20an%20expedited%20process%20for%20approving%20new%20power%20generation%20by%20a%20utility%20that%20wants%20to%20connect%20large%20energy%20loads%20like%20a%20data%20center%2C%20which%20Inskeep%20worried%20wouldn't%20allow%20enough%20time%20for%20public%20input.%20The%20coalition%20also%20wants%20lawmakers%20to%20eliminate%20provisions%20allowing%20utilities%20to%20seek%20permission%20from%20state%20regulators%20to%20recover%20up%20to%20100%25%20of%20the%20costs%20of%20building%20small%20nuclear%20reactors%20from%20customers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20need%20state%20policymakers%20to%20be%20thinking%20about%20these%20issues%20in%20a%20comprehensive%20way%2C%26quot%3B%20Inskeep%20said.%20%26quot%3BBut%20we%20want%20to%20make%20sure%20what%20they%20do%20doesn't%20create%20more%20harm%20than%20good.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIndiana%20Gov.%20Mike%20Braun%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.tristatehomepage.com%2Fnews%2Findiana-news%2Fgovernor-braun-hesitant-on-rate-payer-burden-for-nuclear-reactors%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etold%20News%2010%20in%20February%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20he%20supported%20nuclear%20power%20but%20that%20utilities%20should%20shoulder%20the%20costs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI'm%20hesitant%20about%20putting%20that%20solely%20on%20the%20back%20of%20the%20ratepayers%2C%26quot%3B%20Braun%20said%2C%20adding%20that%20the%20utility%20companies%20will%20have%20to%20absorb%20those%20costs%20through%20%26quot%3Bcapitalism.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThey%20are%20out%20there%20as%20investor%20owned%2C%20and%20some%20of%20that%20is%20going%20to%20have%20to%20be%20the%20risk%20that%20they%20take%2C%26quot%3B%20Braun%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20bill%20passed%20the%20House%20on%20February%2013%20and%20was%20referred%20to%20a%20Senate%20committee.%20The%20Indiana%20legislature%20is%20in%20session%20through%20April.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20the%20data%20center%20boom%20shows%20no%20signs%20of%20slowing%20in%20Indiana%20and%20across%20the%20US%2C%20including%20from%20foreign%20investors%20eager%20to%20get%20a%20stake%20in%20the%20AI%20race.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHussain%20Sajwani%2C%20a%20real%20estate%20tycoon%20dubbed%20the%20%26quot%3BDonald%20of%20Dubai%2C%26quot%3B%20has%20business%20deals%20with%20Trump%20and%20Elon%20Musk.%20Whether%20Sajwani's%20planned%20%2420%20billion%20investment%20in%20data%20centers%20is%20getting%20underway%20in%20Indiana%20is%20unclear%2C%20but%20for%20Inskeep%2C%20it%20wasn't%20surprising.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOh%2C%20here%20comes%20another%20one%2C%26quot%3B%20Inskeep%20said%20of%20his%20initial%20reaction.%20%26quot%3BAt%20this%20moment%20in%20time%2C%20we're%20just%20seeing%20so%20many%20data%20centers%20flood%20into%20Indiana%20that's%20a%20bit%20overwhelming.%20And%20it's%20really%20hard%20to%20fathom%20the%20magnitude%20of%20the%20impacts.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGoogle%20declined%20BI's%20request%20to%20comment%2C%20Microsoft%20didn't%20respond%2C%20and%20Amazon%20and%20the%20Data%20Cent