to%20improving%20government%20efficiency.%20Trump%20has%20fired%20more%20than%20a%20dozen%20inspectors%20general%20as%20part%20of%20the%20purge%20of%20government%20workers.%20And%20Musk%20has%20painted%20federal%20workers%20as%20his%20enemies%20rather%20than%20his%20partners.%20For%20two%20weekends%20in%20a%20row%20DOGE%20has%20sent%20an%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdoge-second-productivity-email-federal-workers-more-soon-2025-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eemail%20to%20all%20federal%20workers%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20asking%20for%20a%20list%20of%20their%20weekly%20accomplishments%3B%20if%20DOGE%20deems%20them%20lacking%20in%20productivity%2C%20they%20could%20be%20terminated.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELast%20month%2C%20onstage%20at%20the%20Conservative%20Political%20Action%20Conference%2C%20Musk%20wielded%20what%20he%20called%20%26quot%3Bthe%20chainsaw%20for%20bureaucracy.%26quot%3B%20But%20if%20Musk%20were%20truly%20interested%20in%20understanding%20the%20government%20to%20root%20out%20inefficiencies%2C%20Bilmes%20says%2C%20the%20memelord%20would%20have%20led%20with%20an%20image%20of%20a%20giant%20ear%20or%20telephone.%20%26quot%3BThe%20wrongheadedness%20of%20the%20approach%20can%20be%20summed%20up%20in%20the%20image%20of%20the%20chainsaw%2C%26quot%3B%20Bilmes%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETwo%20business%20school%20professors%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EI%20talked%20to%20said%20the%20imagery%20harked%20back%20to%20%26quot%3BChainsaw%26quot%3B%20Al%20Dunlap.%20In%20the%201990s%2C%20Dunlap%20wiped%20out%20thousands%20of%20employees%20at%20the%20toilet-paper%20giant%20Scott%2C%20facilitated%20the%20sale%20of%20the%20company%2C%20and%20walked%20off%20with%20a%20%24100%20million%20paycheck.%20Dunlap%20then%20took%20his%20brutal%20methods%20to%20the%20appliance%20maker%20Sunbeam%2C%20where%20share%20prices%20soared%20in%20anticipation%20of%20his%20plan%20to%20halve%20the%20company's%20staff.%20But%20that%20alone%20couldn't%20save%20Sunbeam.%20After%20several%20quarters%20of%20disappointing%20profits%20and%20a%20scandal%20involving%20falsified%20accounting%20documents%2C%20Dunlap%20was%20fired.%20Sunbeam%20went%20bankrupt%2C%20and%20Dunlap%20was%20hit%20with%20a%20shareholder%20lawsuit%20accusing%20him%20of%20inflating%20stock%20prices%20to%20acquire%20two%20other%20brands%2C%20as%20well%20as%20fines%20by%20the%20Securities%20and%20Exchange%20Commission%2C%20which%20accused%20him%20of%20misrepresenting%20Sunbeam's%20financial%20results.%20(He%20settled%20both.)%20All%20that%20chainsawing%20left%20a%20trail%20of%20destruction.%20%26quot%3BHe%20substituted%20one%20kind%20of%20trauma%20for%20another%20kind%20of%20trauma%2C%26quot%3B%20Morris%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMusk%20is%20jogging%20memories%20of%20Chainsaw%20Al%20because%20his%20tactics%20aren't%20about%20simply%20cutting%20back%20on%20government%20waste%2C%20which%20can%20be%20achieved%20through%20things%20such%20as%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-instructs-treasury-stop-producing-new-penny-2025-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ekilling%20the%20penny%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20(Trump%20did%20order%20this)%2C%20getting%20rid%20of%20unoccupied%20office%20space%2C%20and%20telling%20the%20Pentagon%20that%20its%20days%20of%20lobster%20dinners%20are%20no%20more.%20It's%20about%20pushing%20the%20federal%20workforce%20to%20the%20brink%20and%20expanding%20the%20power%20of%20the%20executive%20branch.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI'm%20both%20appalled%20and%20hopeful%2C%26quot%3B%20Morris%20says.%20%26quot%3BLetting%20young%20kids%20who%20don't%20know%20anything%20about%20the%20context%20just%20gain%20access%20to%20all%20kinds%20of%20records%20that%20it's%20not%20clear%20they're%20legally%20allowed%20to%20be%20looking%20at%2C%20that%20opens%20the%20door%20to%20privacy%20issues%2C%20to%20espionage%2C%20to%20all%20kinds%20of%20problems.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20Morris%20maintains%20some%20optimism%20that%20Musk's%20wrecking-ball%20approach%20may%20still%20be%20the%20best%20bet%20yet%20to%20break%20through%20entrenched%20government%20waste.%20%26quot%3BBureaucracies%20grow%20because%20politicians%20make%20calculated%20moves%20based%20on%20the%20constituencies%20that%20they're%20trying%20to%20keep%20for%20the%20next%20election.%20You%20have%20inertia%2C%20you%20have%20this%20snowballing%20bureaucracy%2C%20and%20that's%20part%20of%20the%20problem%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20says.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20relatively%20rare%20to%20have%20an%20administration%20and%20an%20administrator%20like%20Elon%20Musk%20with%20complete%20political%20courage%2C%20political%20recklessness%20even.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20world's%20richest%20man%20doesn't%20answer%20to%20voters%2C%20and%20he%20even%20said%20during%20Trump's%20campaign%20that%20Americans%20should%20expect%20economic%20%26quot%3Bhardship%26quot%3B%20as%20a%20result%20of%20his%20slicing%20of%20government%20programs%20and%20workers.%20And%20Trump%20is%20only%20giving%20Musk%20more%20power%2C%20requiring%20agencies%20to%20create%20a%20centralized%20system%20managed%20by%20DOGE%20where%20they%20record%20and%20justify%20payments.%20He%20has%20even%20said%20he'd%20like%20for%20Musk%20to%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-musk-doge-aggressive-federal-spending-cuts-2025-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eget%20more%20aggressive%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMorris%20says%20that%20when%20bold%20figures%20like%20Musk%20try%20to%20bring%20about%20rapid%20change%20in%20business%2C%20they%20create%20shocks%20to%20the%20system%20that%20usually%20lead%20to%20blowback.%20And%20that%20blowback%20is%20building.%20On%20Thursday%2C%20a%20federal%20judge%20issued%20a%20temporary%20restraining%20order%20blocking%20the%20firing%20of%20probationary%20employees%20at%20some%20agencies.%20DOGE%20is%20drawing%20ire%20not%20just%20from%20federal%20workers%20and%20Democrats%20but%20from%20within%20the%20MAGA%20movement.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Funherd.com%2F2025%2F02%2Fsteve-bannon-is-ready-for-war%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3ESteve%20Bannon%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20has%20called%20Musk%20a%20%26quot%3Btruly%20evil%20person%26quot%3B%20and%20last%20week%20told%20an%20interviewer%20that%20Musk%20%26quot%3Bwants%20to%20impose%20his%20freak%20experiments%20and%20play-act%20as%20God%20without%20any%20respect%20for%20the%20country's%20history%2C%20values%20or%20traditions.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERecently%2C%20federal%20workers%20were%20sent%20a%20now%20notorious%20email%20asking%20them%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fread-email-doge-office-sent-federal-employees-monitor-productivity-2025-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ewhat%20they%20accomplished%20in%20the%20past%20week%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%20They%20had%20little%20time%20to%20respond%2C%20with%20the%20threat%20of%20termination%20hanging%20over%20them%20if%20they%20left%20the%20email%20on%20read.%20Chaos%20ensued.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffederal-workers-react-frustration-fear-doge-productivity-email-2025-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EFederal%20workers%20felt%20harassed%20and%20intimated%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20many%20mulled%20resignation.%20Management%20experts%20largely%20told%20my%20colleagues%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbusiness-leaders-react-elon-musk-doge-management-tactics-federal-emails-2025-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ethis%20type%20of%20leadership%20was%20harmful%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20could%20hurt%20worker%20morale.%20Then%20another%20email%20hit%20workers'%20inboxes%2C%20asking%20for%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpete-hegseth-dod-civilian-workers-reply-doge-productivity-email-2025-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Elist%20of%20accomplishments%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20be%20sent%20every%20Monday.%20The%20emails%20are%20just%20the%20latest%20example%20of%20the%20ways%20DOGE%20and%20the%20Trump%20administration%20have%20wreaked%20psychological%20havoc%20on%20government%20workers%2C%20and%20Bilmes%20described%20them%20as%20%26quot%3Btotal%20nonsense.%26quot%3B%20Many%20workers%20in%20the%20government%20are%20focused%20on%20preventing%20bad%20outcomes%2C%20such%20as%20the%20spread%20of%20disease%20or%20terrorist%20attacks%20%E2%80%94%20that%20work%20doesn't%20necessarily%20lend%20itself%20to%20ideals%20of%20efficiency.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJoseph%20Fuller%2C%20a%20professor%20of%20management%20practice%20at%20Harvard%20Business%20School%2C%20says%20that%20DOGE's%20tactics%20largely%20show%20that%20%26quot%3Bat%20the%20root%20of%20what%20they're%20trying%20to%20do%2C%20they're%20trying%20to%20get%20the%20data.%26quot%3B%20That%20could%20allow%20the%20government%20to%20push%20toward%20automating%20more%20tasks%20of%20its%20office%20workers.%20%26quot%3BIn%20some%20ways%2C%20what%20they're%20trying%20to%20do%20is%20get%20a%20better%20map%20of%20how%20these%20places%20work%20so%20that%20they%20can%20start%20using%20tech%20to%20reduce%20costs%20and%20reduce%20deficits%2C%26quot%3B%20Fuller%20says.%20But%20the%20disarray%20and%20confusion%20created%20by%20DOGE's%20tactics%20could%20outweigh%20any%20benefit.%20%26quot%3BThe%20extent%20to%20which%20that%20agenda%20is%20overthrown%20by%20this%20kind%20of%20almost%20comically%20clumsy%20initiative%20might%20be%20something%20they%20regret%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFuller%20says%20tactics%20similar%20to%20the%20accomplishments%20emails%20happen%20in%20the%20corporate%20world%20in%20companies%20%26quot%3Bunder%20pretty%20significant%20financial%20duress.%26quot%3B%20%26quot%3BIt's%20a%20little%20bit%20of%20a%20'break%20glass%2C%20pull%20lever'%20mechanism%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20says%2C%20that%20%26quot%3Bcan%20be%20useful%20to%20allow%20you%20to%20make%20rapid%20cuts%2C%20which%20might%20cause%20you%20to%20live%20to%20fight%20another%20day%20in%20a%20corporate%20setting.%26quot%3B%20The%20federal%20workforce%20is%20heavily%20unionized.%20The%20sources%20of%20funding%20are%20not%20controlled%20by%20a%20CEO.%20The%20government%20is%20not%20a%20company%20that%20needs%20to%20make%20it%20through%20the%20next%20quarter%20in%20hopes%20of%20being%20acquired.%20It%20needs%20the%20resources%20to%20carry%20on%20in%20perpetuity.%20%3Cspan%3EDOGE%20did%20not%20respond%20to%20questions%20about%20whether%20it%20plans%20to%20work%20with%20the%20GAO%20as%20it%20continues%20to%20recommend%20spending%20cuts%20going%20forward.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20federal%20government%20isn't%20Sunbeam.%20Or%20Twitter.%20Or%20Tesla.%20Or%20SpaceX.%20When%20you%20cut%20half%20the%20people%20who%20work%20at%20Twitter%2C%20it%20glitches%20%E2%80%94%20even%20if%20it%20eventually%20recovers.%20When%20you%20eliminate%20USAID%2C%20people%20can%20die.%20How%20are%20we%20to%20measure%20the%20efficiency%20of%20programs%20that%20keep%20the%20country%20safe%20from%20terrorist%20attacks%20or%20nuclear%20disasters%3F%20The%20purge%20of%20employees%20can%20lead%20to%20gaps%20in%20systems%20we%20can't%20afford%20to%20break%20now%20and%20fix%20later.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20US%20government%20is%20not%20a%20corporation.%20And%20it's%20not%20a%20startup%2C%20the%20vast%20majority%20of%20which%20fail.%20Some%20are%20acquired%2C%20which%20is%20seen%20as%20success.%20Few%20turn%20out%20like%20Tesla%20and%20SpaceX.%20Their%20founders%20move%20on%20to%20try%20again%2C%20to%20come%20up%20with%20something%20new%20and%20take%20it%20back%20to%20investors%20for%20another%20go.%20The%20government%20cannot%20be%20put%20to%20the%20same%20tests%20%E2%80%94%20what%20it%20does%20is%20too%20important.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fauthor%2Famanda-hoover%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cu%