%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.com%2Fnews%2Fvideos%2Fckg84kpw5jwo%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Calling%20Someone%20'Miyan-Tiyan'%2C%20'Pakistani'%20Not%20An%20Offence%3A%20Supreme%20Court%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EThe%20Supreme%20Court%20on%20Tuesday%20ruled%20that%20calling%20someone%20'Miyan-Tiyan'%20or%20'Pakistani'%20may%20be%20in%20poor%20taste%20but%20does%20not%20amount%20to%20an%20offence%20of%20hurting%20religious%20sentiments.%20A%20bench%20of%20Justices%20BV%20Nagarathna%20and%20Satish%20Chandra%20Sharma%20made%20the%20observation%20while%20closing%20a%20case%20against%20a%20man%20accused%20of%20calling%20a%20government%20servant%20'Pakistani'.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20complaint%20was%20filed%20by%20an%20Urdu%20translator%20and%20an%20acting%20clerk%20in%20Jharkhand.%20According%20to%20the%20complainant%2C%20when%20he%20visited%20the%20accused%20to%20furnish%20information%20about%20a%20Right%20To%20Information%20(RTI)%20application%2C%20the%20latter%20abused%20him%20by%20referring%20to%20his%20religion%20and%20used%20criminal%20force%20to%20prevent%20the%20discharge%20of%20his%20official%20duties.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20led%20to%20a%20first%20information%20report%20against%20the%20man%20for%20offences%20under%20Sections%20298%20(hurting%20religious%20sentiments)%2C%20504%20(insult%20with%20intent%20to%20provoke%20breach%20of%20peace)%2C%20and%20353%20(assault%20or%20criminal%20force%20to%20deter%20public%20servant%20from%20discharging%20duty)%20of%20the%20Indian%20Penal%20Code%20(IPC).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETurning%20down%20an%20order%20by%20the%20Jharkhand%20High%20Court%2C%20the%20top%20court%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BThe%20appellant%20is%20accused%20of%20hurting%20the%20religious%20feelings%20of%20the%20informant%20by%20calling%20him%20'Miyan-Tiyan'%20and%20'Pakistani'.%20Undoubtedly%2C%20the%20statements%20made%20are%20in%20poor%20taste.%20However%2C%20it%20does%20not%20amount%20to%20hurting%20the%20religious%20sentiments%20of%20the%20informant%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20bench%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20top%20court%2C%20there%20was%20no%20act%20on%20the%20accused's%20part%20that%20could%20have%20provoked%20a%20breach%20of%20peace.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BEvidently%2C%20there%20was%20no%20assault%20or%20use%20of%20force%20by%20the%20appellant%20to%20attract%20Section%20353%20IPC%20(assault%20or%20criminal%20force%20to%20deter%20public%20servant%20from%20discharging%20duty)%2C%26quot%3B%20it%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1741069740000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2025-03%2F07o74n2_supreme-court_625x300_01_March_25.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fcalling-someone-miyan-tiyan-pakistani-not-an-offence-supreme-court-7843720%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22A%20Supreme%20Court%20bench%20made%20the%20observation%20while%20closing%20a%20case%20against%20a%20man%20accused%20of%20calling%20a%20government%20servant%20'Pakistani'.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fcalling-someone-miyan-tiyan-pakistani-not-an-offence-supreme-court-7843720%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Samay%20Raina%20is%20depressed%2C%20broken%20after%20IGL%20controversy%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1741069689000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-118701222%2Cimgsize-13452.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fentertainment%2Fhindi%2Fbollywood%2Fnews%2Fsamay-raina-is-depressed-after-the-whole-indias-got-latent-controversy-says-his-friend-youtuber-shwetabh-gangwar-toota-hua-hai-woh-insaan%2Farticleshow%2F118701234.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20border%3D%5C%220%5C%22%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fphoto%2F118701234.cms%5C%22%20hspace%3